&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;4-7 years as a transactional attorney with experience on commercial paper of all types&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;A wonkish interest in transactional work and technology law of all sorts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent grasp of on-prem and SaaS transactions, from macro-structural issues and mechanics to accounting nuances&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent negotiation skills including first-hand experience of leading negotiations with parties across multiple jurisdictions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;An empathetic approach to the practice and a spirit of collaboration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ability to perform as part of a diverse team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Flexible, personable, and enjoys a dynamic corporate culture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Excellent organizational skills, including attention to detail and ability to define specific action plans based on general guidance and deliver results&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Strong intellectual capacity, judgment, and personal standards of excellence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Understand how to translate business needs into contract language, including creativity in finding solutions to help resolve business issues&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;A joy and passion for the craft of writing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;An interest in open source software and licensing nuances&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Software engineering skills aren&#39;t required, but a basic understanding of software coding is a definite plus. The GitHub legal team has technical acumen, and a capacity to quickly learn new business and technology concepts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Candidates must have legal authorization to work in the United States&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Tailored cover letter and résumé are required for application to be reviewed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitHub is the best place to share code with friends, co-workers, classmates, and complete strangers. Over 27 million people use GitHub to build amazing things together across 79 million repositories. With the collaborative features of GitHub.com and GitHub Business, it has never been easier for individuals and teams to write faster, better code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We Value:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/em&gt; We believe the best work is done together. &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Empathy:&lt;/em&gt; We believe in putting people first. &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Quality:&lt;/em&gt; We believe in setting the standard for excellence. &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Positive Impact:&lt;/em&gt; We believe in making the world a better place through our work. &lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shipping:&lt;/em&gt; We believe in creating things for the people using them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why You Should Join:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At GitHub, we constantly strive to create an environment that allows our employees (Hubbers) to do the best work of their lives. We&#39;ve designed one of the coolest workspaces in San Francisco (HQ), where over half of our Hubbers work, snack, and create daily. The other half of our Hubbers work remotely in 18 countries across the globe. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/about/careers/remote&quot;&gt;Here is a complete list of where we can hire!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also committed to keeping Hubbers healthy, motivated, focused and creative. We&#39;ve designed our top-notch benefits program with these goals in mind. In a nutshell, we&#39;ve built a place where we truly love working, we think you will too.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitHub is made up of people from a wide variety of backgrounds and lifestyles. We embrace diversity and invite applications from people of all walks of life. We don&#39;t discriminate against employees or applicants based on gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, race, religion, age, national origin, citizenship, disability, pregnancy status, veteran status, or any other differences. Also, if you have a disability, please let us know if there&#39;s any way we can make the interview process better for you; we&#39;re happy to accommodate!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/about/careers/remote&quot;&gt;Where We Can Hire&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note that benefits vary by country, if you have any questions, please don&#39;t hesitate to ask your Talent Partner. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-POST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GitHub Education launched in 2012 with the mission of empowering student developers. Six years later, the program has enabled more than 1 million students to learn to code with real-world tools. The team has grown to accommodate the needs of university students, bootcamp learners, schools and teachers at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now we seek a Associate Program Manager - Education to support our teacher- and student-facing programs. If you want to serve the next generation of developers, and help students level up with real-world tools, we’d love to talk to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitHub Education is a support-driven team. We believe every interaction--from email to Twitter to in-person events- is an opportunity to surprise and delight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is vital to the long-term success of GitHub Education, and will report to the General Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities: &lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help education users make their best work. When folks write in with questions about the Student Developer Pack, GitHub Education for schools, Campus Experts and Campus Advisors, you will have the answers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write for clarity and for empathy. We help students and teachers all over the world. You’ll be working to understand their context, their needs, their problems, and suggest concrete next steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spot patterns, (and then identify solutions). If you hear a problem once, you’ll make a note of it. If you hear it 10 times, you will come up with ideas to help improve our products and programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve our Education offerings through incremental changes to our process for events, swag shipment, communication and outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Qualifications: &lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathy for developers: a background in software development is not required, but you will need to know where developers struggle, and where they might need help.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to identify the root cause of a problem: You know which diagnostic questions to ask, especially with complex issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The motivation to fix problems when you see them: Not only can you identify the root cause of a problem, you can prototype solutions and implement them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A precise and accurate writing style: You can craft a crisp sentence, and words are one of your key strengths.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capacity to work independently: GitHub Education is a remote team, so you will be trusted to deliver at a high degree of excellence as a self-starter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a support or operations role, bonus if it’s working with developer tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for Education. You want to serve the next generation of developers, and help them make their best work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve participated in technical student communities (especially in a leadership capacity).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve taught or have classroom experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience writing documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are organized, and know how to make a system that just works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
