&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are looking to hire a Lead to drive GitHub’s corporate development efforts. As the first dedicated corporate development hire, the successful candidate will have the opportunity operate with autonomy to establish best practices and processes that will prepare the function for future scale. This role will regularly interface with our Executive Team and cross-functional partners in Product and Engineering to take lead on identifying, evaluating, negotiating with, and ultimately integrating acquisition targets. We’re looking for a strategic thinker with strong modeling and deal experience who can drive multiple high-priority projects simultaneously.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideate &amp;amp; Meet. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Take a thematic approach to map the software development ecosystem. Develop market theses alongside Product &amp;amp; Engineering counterparts to identify, classify, and recommend potential acquisition targets. Source opportunities by building and nurturing ongoing relationships with startups, investment bankers, and investors in the industry.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Valuation &amp;amp; Communication. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Own creation of valuation models to evaluate the viability of each transaction and communicate them succinctly to senior leadership. Work with Product &amp;amp; Engineering to identify potential gaps/accelerants in our roadmaps and perform build vs. partner vs. buy analysis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deal Ownership. &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Lead a cross-functional team through the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;corporate development process from end-to-end, acting as the project manager during negotiation, due diligence, and integration.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Playbook.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Own the creation and evolution of GitHub’s corporate development playbook -- continuously refining valuation methodologies, negotiation strategies, deal structures, and integration processes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s degree.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; 4+ years of relevant work experience at a leading investment bank, Venture Capital / Private Equity firm, and/or in corporate development team at a SaaS / Internet company.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Experience.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Extensive competency in building company valuation models and fluency in Corporate Finance. Familiarity with the software development ecosystem is a plus.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Self Starter Mentality&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;. Proactive thinker determined to build processes that scale and provide a solid foundation for long term growth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication Skills. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Distill and simplify complex financial concepts for all audiences.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interpersonal Skills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; Build trust and effectively collaborate cross-functionally. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
