&lt;p&gt;GitHub helps companies and organizations succeed by allowing them to build better software, together. We&#39;re looking for a Corporate Sales Representative who will work with our customers to build great relationships, help them to learn about GitHub, our products and facilitate the buying process. We care about customer success, customer service, and we&#39;re extremely passionate about the quality of our work. The ideal candidate will have the aptitude and passion to become a master of GitHub’s product capabilities, underlying technology, and competitive advantages. Most importantly, the candidate will help our customers achieve their strategic objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for Corporate Sales Representatives to be based in Sydney and cover the following territories: North Asia (incorporating China, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macau and South Korea).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work all mid-market qualified leads and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primary interface to prospects and customers; assist buying process including answering questions and providing information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with customers to communicate how GitHub Enterprise can fit with their business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaison with technical sales team for all technical questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with demos and trials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing quotes and negotiating close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with GitHub tools and technology to keep accurate prospect and customer information and forecast information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a named list of existing accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in regional community engagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with existing regional partners assisting in closing new business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of successful sales experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer orientation, dedication, and passion for delivering a great customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assess customer needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and team oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in Git and GitHub&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical aptitude and the ability to become deeply fluent in the GitHub&#39;s technology and the industry&lt;/li&gt;
