&lt;p&gt;Developers all over the world flock to GitHub to work together on software projects. They come to thrive as developers, to learn, to iterate and improve. They come to build software together in a well structured collaborative environment with processes that are efficient and smooth. Supporting developers in all of this is our mandate; GitHub is the super maintainer of software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The A-B-C of functioning as the super maintainer of software is building an incredible product and supporting a robust platform. Intrinsic to this effort is a responsibility to lead change in the policy environment—laws, regulations, norms, and standard practices—to optimize it for software and developers—our users and customers. GitHub is uniquely positioned to bridge the challenges of collective action and represent the multitudes of developers in policy debates that directly affect their future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitHub is the gateway for software development. Our impact and customers are global, and so is our vision. We&#39;re looking for a technologist who will materially contribute to our vision by helping ground our policy initiatives with detailed, innovative, and technically astute analysis and engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A cover letter is required. A crisp cover letter, preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed analyses of how a wide range and rapidly shifting policy proposals impact software developers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and contribute to blog posts, presentations, amicus briefs, educational materials, working documents/spreadsheets/databases supporting/resulting from above analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate technologies as needed to understand their potential policy impacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to/help maintain policy-relevant internal and public open source repositories and software tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fast, accurate, precise writer on technical and policy topics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid high-level understanding of how computer programs, the web, the internet, etc., work, and demonstrated ability to quickly learn details of any info technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional software development experience, or equivalent (e.g., substantial open source contributions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Loves reading, dissecting, editing, and understanding from all sides policy documents such as those related to legislation, court cases, regulations, standards, site policies, licenses, policy-enacting software code, academic papers, and datasets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
