&lt;p&gt;GitHub’s vision is to supercharge our services with data in order to democratize software engineering worldwide. We seek to enable more people to engage in the creation of code and to participate in the future both creatively and economically. Doing so requires that we make it easier, safer, faster, and more expressive to create and understand code, and enable people to connect with each other and with code projects more effectively. Only this commitment will allow us to realize the significant opportunities before us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitHub has one of the largest and richest software-related data sets on the planet. Achieving our goals involves unifying and learning on top of that data at massive scale. This data includes code, git graphs of code changes, comments, pull requests, issues, users, contributors, and metadata, including languages/frameworks, ASTs and diffs, module and dependency graphs, and annotations from non-user agents like CI systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given the broad scope of our machine learning domain and data sources, a leader in this area must be able to review and assess techniques, models, and frameworks in a fast moving field, and help guide the team toward well reasoned and pragmatic approaches to generating and validating results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the leader of this team you will build and maintain the data sets and models that engineers inside and outside the company build upon. You will collaborate with engineering and product leadership to deliver the capabilities described above. You and your team will be responsible for helping the company achieve key strategic initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities Include:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with Product Management on long term vision, roadmap priorities, and product lifecycle from model formulation through product integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving infrastructure requirements to support learning on top of large data sets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and assess techniques, models, and frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with engineering and product leaders to ensure alignment across functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setting guidelines for use cases that require machine learning vs. other methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promoting team growth via coaching, mentoring, and new opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staffing and shaping the machine learning team to increase team impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing execution and communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years of experience managing and growing software engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise and experience in Machine Learning theory and methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of high impact delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An innovation mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to balance near term product feature work and long term research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of partnership with engineering and product leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading projects and teams on machine learning projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about crafting and fostering good engineering practices and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lead a diverse set of geographically distributed engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
