&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the definition of problems-to-solve on behalf of the customer for your area ensuring it aligns with the overall product and company vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in calls, answer support tickets, and attend enterprise briefings to support our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build cross functional relationships to represent platform needs and requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the point person for projects from start to finish.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with marketing and sales to launch your team’s work in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex, cross-functional projects across multiple teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach, mentor and help set strategy for more junior PMs on the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in Product Management or equivalent experience with demonstrated ability to discover the problem to solve for customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with developer tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of API design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer and stakeholder empathy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with modern software development lifecycle practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to lead multidisciplinary teams and projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
