&lt;p&gt;GitHub is looking for a Senior Software Developer to join our Developer Confidence group. This group is responsible for the build and developer environment functions for our internal teams. The role will focus on frontend development for several internal tools/services and work with our teams to offer an amazing and improved user experience. This person will work multi-functional areas with our Platform Engineering teams to improve and in some cases design for better usability across all our internal applications and workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitHub is committed to building a diverse workforce and strongly encourages applications from people of color and other groups currently underrepresented in tech. Do you think this is the job for you? Are you ready for an amazing career that impacts our industry? We are looking for you to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Display a strong dedication to building an inclusive tech environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have shown resilience and resourcefulness both in and outside of the workplace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can bring a new perspective based on educational, professional and lived experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can effectively communicate with people from disparate backgrounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience mentoring/coaching/teaching, particularly in environments with diverse students/participants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;user-content-responsibilities&quot; class=&quot;anchor&quot; href=&quot;https://github.com/github/engineering/blob/master/interviewing/prod-devcon-ux/job-description.md#responsibilities&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain Rails applications, participate in quality improvement activities, user interface software development and perform code reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain systems built on off-the-shelf solutions and in-house applications, both developed in-house and commercial off the shelf solutions such as (but not limited to) Docker, Jenkins, Slack, Elastic Search and Data Dog.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and develop usability studies and user experience improvements on front-end applications, chatops interfaces and command line interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with on-call engineers to continuously improve alert health for all supporting systems and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review events that impact availability and performance and guide process changes to increase resilience of systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in an on-call rotation for owned services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
